                    <!--Sharepoint's placeholder-->

                    
	
	

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><div class="splash-wrapper splash-contracts"><div class="splash-hero">&#160;<br></div><div class="container splash-top-content"><h1 class="hTitle">We Can Help Your Firm Get Positioned to Compete for Government&#160;Contracts</h1><p>We can help you obtain certification as a&#160;<span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">minority,</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">&#160;</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">w</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">oman</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">,&#160;</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">o</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">r Service-Disabled V</span><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">eteran-owned or an emerging small business</span> and&#160;introduce you to our government contracting assistance experts.<br></p></div><div class="container splash-stripe-white"><h2 class="hSection" style="font-family&#58;arial, sans-serif;color&#58;#333333;">Certification Office for Business, Inclusion, Diversity (COBID)<br></h2><p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;">The primary goal of&#160;<a href="/biz/programs/COBID/Pages/default.aspx" style="color&#58;#333333;text-decoration-line&#58;underline;">COBID</a>&#160;certification is to level the playing field by providing certified firms a fair opportunity to compete for government contracts regardless of owner ethnicity, gender, disability, or firm size.</p><ul class="horz-links"><li style="font-size&#58;1.3em;"> 
            <a href="https&#58;//oregon4biz.diversitysoftware.com/FrontEnd/VendorSearchPublic.asp?XID=6787&amp;TN=oregon4biz">Directory of Certified Firms</a></li><li style="font-size&#58;1.3em;"> 
            <a href="/biz/programs/COBID/Pages/default.aspx">COBID Information</a></li><li style="font-size&#58;1.3em;"> 
            <a href="/biz/programs/COBID/Pages/default.aspx">Certification Resources</a><br></li></ul><h2 class="hSection" style="font-family&#58;arial, sans-serif;color&#58;#333333;">Apex Accelerator (formerly the Government Contracting Assistance Program)<br></h2><p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;">Assistance from 
         <a href="https&#58;//www.orapexaccelerator.org/">Apex Accelerator</a> (formerly the 
         <a href="/biz/programs/GCAP/Pages/default.aspx">Government Contracting Assistance Program</a> [GCAP]) has resulted in hundreds of millions of dollars in contract awards in Oregon. A program of the Organization for Economic Initiatives (OEI), Apex Accelerator provides technical assistance to small businesses to obtain contracts with the federal government.&#160;&#160;<br></p><h2 class="hSection" id="opps">OregonBuys and Contracting Opportunities at Business Oregon<br></h2>
      <strong>&#160;</strong> 
      <p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;"> 
         <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
            <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
               <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
                  <span style="font-weight&#58;700;"></span></span></span></span>
         <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">Business Oregon has the below contracting opportunities open. Visit the state’s web-based eProcurement System, 
            <a href="https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/">OregonBuys</a>. Register today and start using OregonBuys for purchasing and supplier activities.<br></span><strong><br>Technical Assistance for Underrepresented Businesses Program Consultant</strong><span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;"></span></p>
      <span><span> 
            <div>
               <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
                  <span style="text-decoration&#58;underline;">Description&#58;</span> The State of Oregon, acting by and through the Oregon Business Development Department is issuing this Intermediate Request for Proposal for a consultant to support its 2025-2027 Technical Assistance for Underrepresented Businesses Program (“TA Program”). The selected consultant will deliver the services needed to plan, organize, and facilitate quarterly and monthly Program meetings with the new 2025-2027 cohort of 28 Program providers, as well as facilitate smaller virtual peer learning sessions for business advisors and staff of TA Program providers. Meetings are expected to occur in-person, virtually, or in a hybrid format, depending on the audience, objectives, and agenda. Session topics will include, but are not limited to, accessing capital, working with stakeholders, resource sharing and best practices, professional development opportunities, networking and peer learning, and presentations from other stakeholders.&#160;<br><br></span></div> 
            <div>
               <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">For more information, please access the solicitation through the <strong>Bid Solicitation Link&#58; <a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/external/bidDetail.sdo?docId%3DS-12300-00015607%26external%3Dtrue%26parentUrl%3Dclose&amp;data=05%7c02%7cSal.MIRAMONTESJR%40biz.oregon.gov%7c83889ce5136f43bb117d08de417fb278%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639020213864139870%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=p4EC%2BXleESvNa1tHqblOsbSkJSnretvwjL/WL7d35XA%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank" title="OregonBuys website direct landing page for the bid solicitation of the TA for Underrepresented Businesses Program Consultant.">S-12300-00015607</a><br></strong><span style="text-decoration&#58;underline;">Proposal Due Date</span>&#58; January 09, 2026, at 12&#58;30 p.m. Pacific Time.<span style="color&#58;#000000;font-family&#58;arial;font-size&#58;13.3333px;"></span><br></span><br></div></span></span> 
      <h2 class="hSection" style="font-family&#58;arial, sans-serif;color&#58;#333333;">Attention Suppliers<br></h2><p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;">Our agency is using the OregonBuys eProcurement System to place purchase orders and process procurement-related purchasing activities. You must have an&#160;OregonBuys&#160;supplier account to continue doing business with us. Visit the&#160;<a href="https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/view/login/login.xhtml" target="_blank" style="color&#58;#333333;text-decoration-line&#58;underline;">OregonBuys webpage</a>&#160;for instructions on registering for a free account, tips for using the system, and the phone number to call if you need help.<br></p><p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;">**If you are interested in receiving your payment using Automated Clearing&#160; House (ACH), please 
         <a href="/das/Financial/AcctgSys/Documents/ACH-Enrollment-Form.pdf" target="_blank"> 
            <img class="ms-asset-icon ms-rtePosition-4" src="/_layouts/images/icpdf.png" alt="" />fill out the this&#160;form</a>.<br></p><p style="font-size&#58;1.3em;"></p></div><div class="splash-stripe-grey contact" id="help"><div class="container"> 
         <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
            <span style="font-size&#58;30px;">
               <a href="/biz/aboutus/contactus/Pages/default.aspx">Contact Us Today</a></span></span> 
         <p> 
            <span style="font-size&#58;18.2px;">
               <strong>Not sure what you need?&#160;</strong>We get it. Give us a call or an email to help see if exporting is a good fit for your business.</span><br></p></div></div>
   <br>
</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6">
